    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Aniket-Engg Thanks for raising this. Unfortunately updating the `Migrations.sol` to latest solc would be a breaking change for users running `truffle init` with earlier versions of truffle. The template for a bare-box project sits [here](https://github.com/truffle-box/bare-box) and is strongly decoupled from truffle itself. At present the best work-around is to update that file following the warnings solc provides - there's just a couple things.  \r\n\r\nWe probably need to implement [truffle-core 117](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-core/issues/117) to manage this requirement appropriately. Another approach that's been discussed is removing `Migrations.sol` from bare projects altogether and having truffle manage that feature 'magically' behind the scenes. ",
